 <br>
Take it from someone who LARPs. Roleplaying only works in an environment where the rules require it. Entropy drags everything down to the lowest allowable point otherwise.<br>
 <br>
RP is either required or you end up with a situation precisely like anywhere else in EQ-which barring the No-drop/language rules is precisely what we have here on FV. People will do what is natural-make friends and try and play the game with the optimal combination. Which is why I can go zone into Dulak's Harbor and see ogres and high elves sitting there cheerfully kicking the crap out of the pirates together.<br>
<br>
Unless the game itself forces people apart (see Dark Ages of Camelot for an example) they will naturally group together to do what the game is about-explore and enjoy.<br>
<br>
Can you RP on Firionia Vie? Sure. Is it a supportive environment to do so anymore? Hell no. <br>
<br>
People want to have fun together,and the game says that it doesn't matter if you're good,evil,or whatever.<br>
 <br>
It -means- nothing. There is no alignment system. No &quot;good people don't get xp helping bad people&quot; or vice versa. I was at a GM event the other week,where halflings were invading Nektulos.<br>
 <br>
I had a real honest-to-goodness halfling and at least two high elves sitting there killing halflings alongside me. No illusion spells either. And the first thing out of people's mouth after the main bad guy died?<br>
 <br>
&quot;What was the loot?&quot;<br>
<br>
Frankly,I wish they'd gone farther with the alignment system. Even made it that certain factions,if raised or lowered too much resulted in swift,divine,and permamently fatal death.<br>
 <br>
The tag is (Roleplayed Preffered) is a joke. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nakath>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/21/03 12:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV lost</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Pfft. FV as a &quot;roleplaying server&quot; died last year around May 8th,when the rules requiring a lot of RP-friendly play were eliminated.<br>
