<br>
Here is a classic case of limited realm of roleplay...<br>
<br>
You can't compare paper RPGS, LARPS, and other things like that to EQ, thats like compairing apples to oranges, and heres why.....<br>
<br>
First of all, EverQuest is a non-liner, non-changing realm.  Monsters are the same, cities, places, events are frozen in time, except for the occasional 24.95 module or GM event that happens once in a blue moon.<br>
<br>
RPG's, Like D&amp;D, Vampire, Rifts, etc... etc... are worlds created by a Dungeon Master, the realm you live in on a paper game is constant changing and you are more physcially involved in the events that change the realm that you walk in.<br>
<br>
EverQuest, you kill a certain major boss, god, etc... grats, he'll be up in 6 days or so, go back and do it again.  Its more in line with the MUD's ((Multi User Dimenisons for those who didn't know the term)) I used to play back in the day.  The realm is limited in that sense, so really, the only Roleplay we have on this server is between character interaction, and not world interaction.  Granted, if you have an imagination, I guess you could raid some city as a group of evils/goods and kill guards and the like, but when your done, the city doesn't change, it stays the same.<br>
<br>
I think the problem with those who want to &quot;roleplay&quot; (using that term lightly) is that they want the world to change with their desires, but its not going to happen.  Basically, what you create in this game is situations between players,and not situations in the world itself.  <br>
<br>
Prime example, Lets say, I, (going to my Bard For a Day Story )  wish to become the leader of the Dismal Rage.  Thats great, maybe in my realm of RP I am, but not every follower of the Dismal Rage is gonna log in and have someone standing there saying, sorry, Pietro Zarn is no longer the SK guildmaster, go look up Kaneer Ca'Vehroe.  Just not going to happen, and will never happen.  The realm of imagination lets you think the things you wish to think, but in the end, just because how you see something, doesn't mean the rest are going to acknowledge it because in their RP, your existance may not even affect their story or their way or roleplay.  <br>
<br>
Thus why if you are going to RP on a EQ server, you have to realise that your story or the way you roleplay isn't going to affect everyone that walks by... and not everyone you interact with is going to be involved in your roleplay either.  I think when people try to involve everyone in their roleplay, they cause all these tizzy fits about good and bad roleplayers...<br>
<br>
One more example before I shut up, Shintou... granted he RP's with everyone, but not everyone is going to RP with him.  Maybe they don't want a Shintou in their RP line, maybe they don't RP at all... who knows, who cares. They spend their money to play this game just like the rest of us and they have that right to do what they please with their time on the server....<br>
<br>
So in conclusion, there is no right or wrong way to roleplay, Whether you wish to do so or not, that is your choice.  But remember, The physical game doesn't change with your characters accomplishments... it stays the same on through time or untill someone at SOE changes it, as where a true RPG does change with your characters accomplishments.  RP here is player interaction, not world interaction, NPC's don't RP with players... just how it is... <br>
<br>
/rant off <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos2/k2_copy.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
